i-globalisation movement, the ‘war on terrorism’, the rise of anti-immigrant racism, and the nihilistic violence which lurks at the margins of the political.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAnti-globalization movement. 0aDemocracy. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 0aPostmodernismxPolitical aspects. 0aPoststructuralismxPolitical aspects. 0aRadicalism. 4aPolitical Studies 2019. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / General.2bisacsh  aMarxist-Leninism.  aclass struggle.  aglobalisation.  aneo-liberal capitalism.  apostmodernity.  apower.  aradical politics.  areligious fundamentalism.  auniversality.  awar on terror.1 aNewman, Saul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779226640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847792266423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847792266/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles